<br>
If you don't understand, I'll explain it again more simply:<br>
<br>
Changes change things. At the moment, in order to succeed as a raiding guild, it is necessary not to care about exp. Caring about exp is a sign of a n00b, and will definitely distract from the goal of the raid.<br>
<br>
But that is with the game system as it is. If it was different, it would be different. Just as when a new expansion comes out, it becomes possible to hunt in new zones, when the game system changes, it becomes worthwhile to raid in new ways.<br>
