<br>
It'd turn into more of a circus than it already is. People that actually needed a reason to raid a zone would just start showing up for the hell of it, to see if their 3 groups can &quot;make some phat xp&quot;. Not having xp be involved in raiding seperates people who care about what they are doing, and have to take the time to do it right, from the overwhelming mass of people whose biggest goal is &quot;d00d, i ned lv 60.&quot;<br>
Knowing that the only thing you may get out of a raid is death is something that turns a large amount of people away from raiding, which I am thankful for. Raidable zones are packed as it is, and telling people they can make xp there in the required large groups that it takes would make ToV into a 230+ people pickup zone. <p>Nenjin Darkeyes<BR>
