<br>
Raids can be as dull, or more dull, than exp grinding, IMHO.  The reward is often totally non-existant for most of the people that attend.  Sharing the exp would at least provide some means of compensation for the time put in by 98% of the raiders that don't end up with loot. <br>
<br>
In Luclin a lot of the zones make it somewhat necessary for 2-3 groups to work together in a mini-raid.  If they could all be linked to share experience it could be a combined mini-raid, exp grouping.  Yet usually one group gets porportionately more kills than the other two.  <br>
<br>
